properties.headline: High Wind Watch issued February 15 at 3:44PM AKST until February 17 at 9:00AM AKST by NWS Anchorage, AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...South winds 40 to 60 mph with gusts up to 80 mph
possible.

* WHERE...Alaska Peninsula from King Cove west including Cold Bay.

* WHEN...From late Sunday night through Monday morning.

* IMPACTS...High winds could move loose debris, damage property,
and cause power outages.
properties.instruction:
A high wind watch means there is potential for a hazardous high
wind event. Monitor the latest forecasts and warnings for updates
on this situation. Fasten loose objects or shelter objects in a
safe location prior to the onset of winds.

NWSheadline: HIGH WIND WATCH IN EFFECT FROM LATE SUNDAY NIGHT THROUGH MONDAY MORNING FROM KING COVE WEST
